Understanding the JVM enables writing performant Java and diagnosing production issues.

```
JVM Memory Layout:
┌─────────────────────────────────────┐
│  Heap: objects, class instances     │
│  ├─ Young Gen (Eden + S0 + S1)      │
│  └─ Old Gen (Tenured)               │
├─────────────────────────────────────┤
│  Stack (per thread): frames,        │
│    local vars, operand stack        │
├─────────────────────────────────────┤
│  Metaspace: class metadata (JDK 8+) │
│  Code Cache: JIT-compiled code      │
└─────────────────────────────────────┘

// GC Roots: local vars, static refs, JNI refs
// Reachable from roots = alive; else eligible for GC

// Tune GC flags:
// -Xms512m -Xmx2g          heap bounds
// -XX:+UseG1GC             G1 garbage collector
// -XX:MaxGCPauseMillis=100 target pause
// -XX:+PrintGCDetails      GC logging

// ClassLoader hierarchy:
// Bootstrap -> Platform -> Application -> Custom
```
JIT compiles hot paths to native code. Profile-guided: interpret first, then compile methods called >10k times.

